Vice President Biden hosted a conference call with the National Governors Association (NGA) leadership to discuss workforce development and job-driven training. He emphasized the importance of providing workers with the skills they need for in-demand jobs and highlighted successful efforts in states across the country. The Vice President also met with leaders from information technology companies to discuss the need for training programs to teach skills that are in demand by employers. He encouraged the leaders to support partnerships with training organizations and community colleges, define common skills and credentials, and increase the number of apprenticeship programs. These meetings are part of Vice President Biden's ongoing work to improve the workforce and training system.